definition: to gain nothing/to end up empty-handed
one/1/single/a (article)/as soon as/entire/whole/all/throughout/"one" radical in Chinese characters (Kangxi radical 1)/also pr. [yao1] for greater clarity when spelling out numbers digit by digit
not to have/no/none/not/to lack/un-/-less
actually/place/classifier for houses, small buildings, institutions etc/that which/particle introducing a relative clause or passive/CL:個|个[ge4]
to catch/to obtain/to capture

sentences.english: The unemployed engineer wrote a dozen applications for jobs but go nothing.
sentences.chinese: 失業的工程師一連寫了十幾封求職信，但一無所獲。

sentences.english: He searched for a flower shop and a local winery and found none.
sentences.chinese: 他想找家花店和當地的葡萄酒廠，但一無所獲。

sentences.english: So Ekman sat and looked at the film. Nothing.
sentences.chinese: 於是埃克曼坐下來仔細觀察影片，可一無所獲。

sentences.english: They searched the house thoroughly,but found nothing.
sentences.chinese: 他們徹底地搜查了房子，但是一無所獲。

sentences.english: Fishing is my favourite sport , I often fish for hours without catching anything .
sentences.chinese: 釣魚是我喜愛的運動，我常垂釣很長時間而一無所獲。

sentences.english: Near sunset, still without a fish, he decided to turn back.
sentences.chinese: 日落時分，他仍一無所獲，便決定打道回府。

sentences.english: But even though scientists spent years looking for genes, they found none that were reproducibly associated with a marked effect.
sentences.chinese: 但儘管研究者們花了數年來尋找這種基因卻一無所獲。

sentences.english: If they simply focus on the technology towards doing that, they will get nothing.
sentences.chinese: 如果他們只是關注於技術層面，那他們將一無所獲。

sentences.english: The job hunter dawdled all morning but achieved nothing.
sentences.chinese: 這個找工作的人閒混了一個上午，一無所獲。

sentences.english: I started by looking at common Spanish websites, but nothing felt quite right.
sentences.chinese: 我開始時在普通的西班牙網站上尋找，但是一無所獲。

sentences.english: Two forehands winner, and nothing to do for me.
sentences.chinese: 兩個正手得分，而我一無所獲。

sentences.english: The police went over his room three times, but found nothing.
sentences.chinese: 警察對他的房間搜查了三次，但一無所獲。

sentences.english: If increased exports are balanced by increased imports, nothing is gained.
sentences.chinese: 如果增加出口與增加的進口相平衡，我們一無所獲。

sentences.english: I'm a scientist. I did literature searches, and nothing could be found.
sentences.chinese: 我是搞科研的，會查些文獻，但是一無所獲。

sentences.english: A man, who wastes all his lifetime, is to throw out gold without buying anything.
sentences.chinese: 虛度一生，就像拋出黃金而一無所獲。

sentences.english: In a more extreme case, simply log out of the BDW entirely.
sentences.chinese: 在更極端的情況下，只需登錄的BDW一無所獲。
